sudo port install git libidl autoconf213 gmake python27 gcc48 freetype 

on Intel, you also need two compilers:

sudo port install yasm clang-3.4

on 10.5 PPC, the 10.4 SDK has some older gcc roots that the ld74-127 linkeer won't like 
too much, so install an older linker on 10.5 PPC and set it to the default:

sudo port -v install ld64-97
sudo port -v install ld64 +ld64_97



And then:

autoconf213
gmake -f client.mk build 

to get more verbose builds, edit client.mk to remove the "-s".

however, doing this all the time may generate errors. To be further evaluated.

--- a/client.mk
+++ b/client.mk
